{
  "texts": [
    "The physical bodies of users of IXR immersed in a virtual environment are still involved in the experience and thus are potentially at risk.",
    "We classify the physical harms of IXR into two categories: incidental and intentional.",
    "Incidental harms arise during the normal use of IXR technology, without any malfunctioning or interference.",
    "For instance, \"cybersickness\" is a well-documented side effect of using VR headsets; symptoms include nausea, headaches, fatigue, and vomiting (Stephen et al., 2020).",
    "Since the 1990s, it has been known to affect women disproportionately (Hayles, 1996; Jasper et al., 2020)."
  ]
}